result.execSummary:
The defendant Shawn S. Zastrow was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Amphetamine(>3-10g) [Modifiers: Repeater, Second and Subsequent Offense, Possession with Intent to Deliver/Distribute a Controlled Substance On or Near a Park], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(e)2.
  • Manuf/Deliver Amphetamine(>3-10g) [Modifiers: Repeater, Second and Subsequent Offense, Possession with Intent to Deliver/Distribute a Controlled Substance On or Near a Park], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(e)2.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Plea Quest/Waiver of Rights & Counsel filed. State moves to DRI 2 & 4 14CF766- crt grants. State moves to DRI 14CM1366 & 14CM1772- crt grants. PLEA: NO CONTEST - cts 1 & 3 - (manuf/deliver ampt/repeater/second & sub offense/on or near a park). Crt advises def of rights & penalties & ques def to understanding.  Crt finds plea & waiver freely & vol made, a factual basis & def guilty.  Statement by State; Defense & Defendant.  COURT ORDERS: WI State Prison 10 yrs Total; Initial Confinement 5 yrs; Extended Supervision 5 yrs, Concurrent to each other. 366 days credit on each count. Crt informs and Defendant signs Voter Ineligibility Notice. Defendant eligible for Challenge Incarceration and Substance Abuse Program. Copy of CR234 given to Defendant after Court.
